metadata.name: No Breathing Space
metadata.description:
The slow drag of life walking by.  
This all ending never beginning,  
Time after time.  
No gumption or motion,  
To bring forth arising devotion.  
To perspire and prepare for the upcoming road ahead,  
No energy left.  
Feeling dead,  
So tired and exhausted.  
Rather stay in bed.

-Seth Milliman

This piece encapsulates a mindstate relatable to all , the downtimes , the moments of sadness , the pain. These are emotions just as valid , and we must accept and process them.
